-- Edelweiss Climbs Most in 19 Months on Company Plan for Stock Split, Bonus
-- Paresh Jatakia
-- 2010-06-21T11:35:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-21/edelweiss-climbs-most-in-19-months-on-company-plan-for-stock-split-bonus.html

          
          
             Edelweiss Capital Ltd. , an Indian
provider of financial services, gained the most in 19 months in
Mumbai trading after saying it will consider splitting its stock
and give free shares to investors.  
 The board of the Mumbai-based company will meet on June 24
to decide on the subdivision and bonus, Edelweiss said in a
statement on June 18 after trading hours.  
 Shares  rose  19.2 percent to 500.70 rupees, the biggest gain
since Nov. 3, 2008, after earlier surging by the daily
permissible limit of 20 percent. The stock was the best
performer on the  BSE500 Index  today, with the trading volume at
33 times the six-month daily average.  
